quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  15,31,"Except Iblees;{1} he refused to be with those who prostrated.",1:[Who was of the jinn.  See 18:50.]
  15,32,"[Allāh] said, "
  15,33,"He said, "
  16,10,"It is He who sends down rain from the sky; from it is drink and from it is foliage in which you pasture [animals]."
  16,11,"He causes to grow for you thereby the crops, olives, palm trees, grapevines, and of all the fruits. Indeed in that is a sign for a people who give thought."
  16,12,"And He has subjected for you the night and day and the sun and moon, and the stars are subjected by His command. Indeed in that are signs for a people who reason."